'It was hard for us to replace Jagoba,' Loren said in an interview with Spanish sports newspaper Marca. 'But the team needed to react and it certainly has done so.

'Our immediate aim has been achieved.

'I think the first thing that David (Moyes) did when he arrived was to try to give the team more solidness and consistency, and you can see that he has achieved that.

'The team is improving.'

Moyes is under contract with Real Sociedad for another season.

