'We were fortunate that a man that initially appeared inaccessible to Real Sociedad, ended up coming here,' Loren said. 'I believe he (Moyes) is giving a big contribution.'

Loren believes the arrival of Moyes will open the door for the arrival of British players to the club in the near future.

'It's difficult to bring players from England, unless you have something that can attract the players,' Loren said. 'With Moyes here, the task of bringing players from there (England) can be made easier.'

Real Sociedad return to La Liga action on Saturday when they play away to Malaga.

